    "body": "This PR aims to support writing high-performance warp-specialized 2cta gemm on Blackwell, optimizing GEMM on (8192, 8192, 8192) to ~1670TFlops. Thanks @Hamerlate for providing the dev machine.\r\n\r\n<!-- This is an auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->\r\n## Summary by CodeRabbit\r\n\r\n* **New Features**\r\n  * Added optional 2-CTA cluster mode for Blackwell GEMM kernels with runtime toggle and new kernel variants\r\n  * New public pass to enable Blackwell 2-CTA lowering\r\n\r\n* **Improvements**\r\n  * Examples updated with persistent and non-persistent single-/2-CTA GEMM variants and runtime selection/benchmarking output\r\n  * Cluster-aware memory/load primitives, swizzle utilities, and synchronization hooks for multi-CTA execution\r\n  * New layout helpers for bank-swizzled buffers and TMA 2SM load helpers (with cache hints)\r\n<!-- end of auto-generated comment: release notes by coderabbit.ai -->",
